================================================================================
  1. LAYOUT & GLOBAL (_Layout.cshtml, screen.css, main.js)
================================================================================

[ ] LAY.1   [P0] ADD DARK / LIGHT MODE TOGGLE
     Currently: Dark mode is hardcoded (class="dark-mode" on <html>). CSS
     supports both themes but there is no toggle in the UI.
     Enhance: Add a sun/moon icon button to .gh-head-actions. On click,
     toggle data-theme attribute on <html> and persist choice in
     localStorage. Respect prefers-color-scheme on first visit.

[ ] LAY.2   [P0] WIRE UP READING PROGRESS BAR
     Currently: .reading-progress element exists in the layout and CSS
     styles are defined, but no scroll event handler activates it. main.js
     is almost entirely a debug/diagnostics tool.
     Enhance: Add scroll listener that calculates read percentage of
     .gh-content on article pages and sets width on .reading-progress-fill.
     Add .visible class when user begins scrolling. Hide on non-article
     pages.

[ ] LAY.3   [P0] WIRE UP BACK-TO-TOP BUTTON
     Currently: #back-to-top button exists in markup and CSS has show/hide
     transitions, but no JS activates it.
     Enhance: Show button after scrolling past 500px. Smooth-scroll to top
     on click. Add .visible class toggle.

[ ] LAY.4   [P0] EMPTY FOOTER "CONNECT" COLUMN
     Currently: The third footer-section has <h4>Connect</h4> with no
     content below it. The 4th column is completely absent.
     Enhance: Populate Connect with social media links pulled from site
     settings (twitter, facebook). Remove or repurpose the empty 4th column
     slot so the grid doesn't show a gap.

[ ] LAY.5   [P1] ADD SKIP-TO-CONTENT ACCESSIBILITY LINK
     Currently: No skip-navigation link for keyboard/screen-reader users.
     Enhance: Add <a href="#site-main" class="sr-only focus:not-sr-only">
     Skip to content</a> as the first child of <body>. Style to appear on
     focus for keyboard users.

[ ] LAY.6   [P1] ADD KEYBOARD SHORTCUT HINT ON SEARCH BUTTON
     Currently: Ctrl/Cmd+K opens search but this is not advertised.
     Enhance: Add a subtle <kbd>⌘K</kbd> badge next to or inside the
     search button. Show Ctrl on Windows, ⌘ on Mac via JS UA detection.

[ ] LAY.7   [P2] ADD PREFERS-REDUCED-MOTION AWARENESS TO JS
     Currently: CSS has prefers-reduced-motion but JS animations (card
     hover translateY, modal slideDown) are not gated.
     Enhance: Check matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)') before
     applying JS-driven transitions.


