  3. POST / ARTICLE PAGE (Post.cshtml)
================================================================================

[ ] POST.1  [P0] ADD SOCIAL SHARE BUTTONS
     Currently: No share functionality on posts at all.
     Enhance: Add a share toolbar below the article title or after the
     article body with buttons for: Twitter/X, LinkedIn, copy link, email.
     Use native Web Share API on mobile as primary, fallback to individual
     links. No third-party scripts — pure URL-based sharing.

[ ] POST.2  [P1] ADD TABLE OF CONTENTS FOR LONG POSTS
     Currently: No auto-generated TOC. CSS already has scroll-margin-top
     on headings for anchor linking.
     Enhance: Auto-generate a floating or collapsible TOC sidebar from
     h2/h3 headings in .gh-content. Highlight the current section on
     scroll. Collapse on mobile to a dropdown. Only show when the post
     has 3+ headings.

[ ] POST.3  [P1] ADD ANCHOR LINKS ON ARTICLE HEADINGS
     Currently: Headings have scroll-margin-top but no clickable anchor or
     id attribute. Readers cannot link to specific sections.
     Enhance: Auto-generate slug-based id attributes on h2/h3 in rendered
     content. Add a hover-visible # link icon before each heading.

[ ] POST.4  [P1] ADD NEWSLETTER CTA BETWEEN AUTHOR BOX AND COMMENTS
     Currently: Post ends with author box → webmentions → comments. No
     inline subscribe prompt for engaged readers.
     Enhance: Insert a subscribe CTA section using the .footer-cta pattern
     after the author card and before the comments section. Show site
     title, "Get the latest posts" copy, and email/subscribe button.

[ ] POST.5  [P1] ADD COMMENT LOADING STATE
     Currently: Comments section shows "Comments (0)" while fetching from
     API, then flickers to actual count. No loading indicator.
     Enhance: Show a skeleton loader or spinner while comments.js fetches.
     Set initial count text to "..." or hide count until loaded.

[ ] POST.6  [P2] ADD COMMENT FORMATTING HELP
     Currently: Comment textarea is plain text with no formatting hints.
     Enhance: Add a small "Basic formatting supported" note below the
     textarea. Optionally add a preview toggle button that renders the
     comment HTML before submission.

[ ] POST.7  [P2] ADD ESTIMATED POSITION INDICATOR
     Currently: Thin progress bar at top of viewport.
     Enhance: Add a "X min left" countdown near the reading time in the
     byline that updates as the user scrolls through the article.


